                                         JOHANNESBURG - Johannesburg Metro Police say that the M2 West highway has been blocked off for traffic at the Crown Interchange. The road's been closed off for maintenance and is likely to only reopened later on Sunday afternoon. Motorists are being urged to use alternative routes. JMPD spokesperson Wayne Minnaar said: “Motorists can only go south and north to join the M2 to Main Reef Road.  Motorists will have to use Carr Street off-ramp and then drive through Fordsburg to join Main Reef Road.”